		<td><b>NES flickering/slowdown gone?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />- I don't know if the term "emulated" is correct, but anyway let's assume it is.
<br />
<br />- The Playstation version of (NES) Mega Man has no sprite flickering or even game slowdowns. Some screen transitions are perfect, meaning no "garbaged" things during that time. Yes, it's a matter of turning off then on the screen while doing a CHR bankswitching... and so on.
<br />
<br />- Any thoughts about eliminating such annoyances while emulating a game?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
