	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's been a while since I've played/read about it, but it's my understanding that the Anniversary Collection NES games are not emulated, but rather rewritten for the target platform. At the very least, the sound isn't emulated, due to the fact that you can rapid-fire an enemy and hear lots of overlapping sound effects (not possible on the NES due to the limited number of channels). Even more telling is the fact that the music eventually fades out and restarts. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


